item.description:
Motivation When working on a project, most of us spend time thinking about what to create (e.g., a cleaned data set, a new algorithm, an analysis, and/or a paper and corresponding slides), but not about how to manage its creation. This results in two major issues, as outlined next.
!!! important &ldquo;Major issues in managing data-intensive projects&rdquo;
- we may lose sight of the project (&quot;directory and file chaos&quot;) - Gradually, we write code and edit data sets, and put those files somewhere on our computer.
